Given that $f(x+6)=f(x)$, we can deduce that $f(x)$ is a periodic function with a period of 6 on $\mathbb{R}$.

When $-3<x\leq-1$, $f(x)=-(x+2)^2$, and when $-1\leq x\leq 3$, $f(x)=x$.

To find $f(1) + f(2) + \dots + f(2015)$, we first examine the sum $f(1) + f(2) + \dots + f(6)$:

\begin{align*}
f(1) + f(2) + \dots + f(6) &= f(1) + f(2) + f(3) + f(-2) + f(-1) + f(0) \\
&= 1 + 2 + 3 + 0 - 1 + 0 \\
&= 5
\end{align*}

Since $f(x)$ has a period of 6, the sum of any 6 consecutive terms will also equal 5.

Now, we can calculate $f(1) + f(2) + \dots + f(2015)$ by finding how many full periods of 6 terms are contained within the sum, and then adding the remaining terms:

\begin{align*}
f(1) + f(2) + \dots + f(2015) &= 335 \times 5 + f(1) + f(2) + f(3) + f(0) + f(-1) \\
&= 1675 + 1 + 2 + 3 + 0 - 1 \\
&= \boxed{1680}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the answer is (C).

